    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Geological Society of London | Somerset House.</placeName>
                    <date>23<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> May 1839</date>
                    <salute>Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                 
<p>I am requested by the Geological Society to express their thanks for your present of Plants in Anthracite from Philadelphia, and Fossils from Cornwall<ref target="#foot.f1"/> and to assure you that the Society are much honored by this mark of consideration.</p>
<p>I have the honour to be, | Sir, | Your most obedient and very humble Servant, | Charles Darwin | Secretary <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To Dr. Mantell</p>
<p>F.G.S. etc.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Mantell presented a ‘Slab with impressions of plants from Philadelphia, and fossils from Cornwall’ to the Society on 22 May 1839 (<hi rend="italic">Transactions of the Geological Society</hi> 2d ser. 5 (1840), list of donations).</note>
        </div>        
            
